  "text": ", using the methods detailed in Table 5 . Atmospheric P deposition for the Arctic is taken from [CITATION_1] . They estimate annual Arctic Ocean atmospheric TP deposition of 6.9 Gg yr À1 , with 2.2 Gg solubilized to SRP (the labile fraction; Table 5 ). These combined P fluxes total 72.6 Gg P yr À1 ; thus, we estimate meltwater runoff from the GrIS constitutes approximately 15% (10.9 Gg yr À1 ) of the labile P flux to the Arctic oceans. More significantly, we estimate that TP fluxes from the ice sheet (~408 Gg yr À1 ) are more than 3 times that of the flux from Arctic rivers (~125 Gg yr",
